of the copyright holder. Citation: IUCN (2017). Gender-responsive restoration guidelines: A closer look at gender in the Restoration Opportunities Assessment Methodology. Gland, Switzerland: IUCN. Cover Photo: iStock Available From: IUCN (International Union for Conservation of Nature) Global Forest and Climate Change Programme Rue Mauverney 28 1196 Gland, Switzerland forests@iucn.org iucn.org/forest Global Gender Office 1630 Connecticut Ave NW #300 Washington, DC 20009, USA gender@iucn.org genderandenvironment.org Introduction ....................................................................................................................................... 1 Why is gender equality and women\u2019s empowerment important for ROAM? ............................. 1 How can ROAM be gender responsive? ................................................................................... 2 Phase 1. Preparation and planning ................................................................................................... 5 Defining the problem, scope and outputs ................................................................................. 5 Engaging key partners ............................................................................................................... 5 Identifying the assessment criteria and indicators .................................................................... 5 Gender situation and analysis .................................................................................................... 6 Identifying data and capacity needs .......................................................................................... 7 Planning for stakeholder engagement ....................................................................................... 7 Organising the inception workshop ........................................................................................... 9 Phase 2. Data collection and analysis ...............................