022 Cultural barriers limiting women\u2019s participation and leadership roles \u2022 Building capacity of NGOs and community organisations to address gender \u2022 Limited time to participate due to already too much workload \u2022 Improving security of tenure for women by planting boundary trees \u2022 Lack of alternative sources of energy and income-generating activities \u2022 Identifying context issues on how women will benefit from REDD+ \u2022 Lack of comprehensive consultations at all levels \u2022 Targeting the education system to include a gender-sensitive ecosystem approach in the curricula \u2022 Few pilot demonstrations targeting women due to few resources \u2022 Reaching women\u2019s movement participants and Uganda Women\u2019s Parliamentary Association to explain climate issues in relation to REDD+ and get their support \u2022 Limited support for women\u2019s initiatives since forestry is low among government priorities \u2022 Consulting with gender and forest task force on laws and policies that relate to women (by REDD+ focal point) \u2022 Planning at the local level not linked to national-level process especially for women \u2022 Identifying the contextual issues in relation to women and harmonising with REDD+ pilots \u2022 Emerging disasters that may affect women, necessitating relocation \u2022 Women in NGOs have insufficient information about REDD+ \u2022 Poor linkages from the local to", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "71673c0e-fcc6-4693-87ed-06a56637fc8b": {"__data__": {"id_": "71673c0e-fcc6-4693-87ed-06a56637fc8b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/gender-responsive-restoration-guidelines", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "exclud